From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 08:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qcom: ppe: edma: ratelimit AXI error prints

`edma_misc_handle_irq()` already wraps every other error-class print
in `net_ratelimit()` — except AXI read and write errors. On IPQ5332
the misc IRQ fires continuously when EDMA HW is in a degraded state
(e.g. once we start dropping RX descriptors via the NULL-skb guard).
Without rate-limiting, the kernel log is flooded fast enough that no
other output gets through, and the rdinit shell is unusable.

Match the existing pattern: gate the AXI error prints on
`net_ratelimit()` too. The percpu stats counters keep updating as
before — only the console spam is suppressed.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
@@ -295,14 +295,16 @@ static irqreturn_t edma_misc_handle_irq(int irq, void *ctx)
 	pr_debug("Received misc irq %d, status: %d\n", irq, misc_intr_status);

 	if (FIELD_GET(EDMA_MISC_AXI_RD_ERR_MASK, misc_intr_status)) {
-		pr_err("MISC AXI read error received\n");
+		if (net_ratelimit())
+			pr_err("MISC AXI read error received\n");
 		u64_stats_update_begin(&stats->syncp);
 		++stats->edma_axi_read_err;
 		u64_stats_update_end(&stats->syncp);
 	}

 	if (FIELD_GET(EDMA_MISC_AXI_WR_ERR_MASK, misc_intr_status)) {
-		pr_err("MISC AXI write error received\n");
+		if (net_ratelimit())
+			pr_err("MISC AXI write error received\n");
 		u64_stats_update_begin(&stats->syncp);
 		++stats->edma_axi_write_err;
 		u64_stats_update_end(&stats->syncp);
